### Conversations API Tests

### POST /api/conversation - Create a new conversation
POST http://localhost:3000/api/conversation
Content-Type: application/json

###

### GET /api/conversation - Get all conversations (default limit 100)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/conversation

###

### GET /api/conversation - Get conversations with custom limit
GET http://localhost:3000/api/conversation?limit=10

###

### GET /api/conversation - Error: Invalid limit (should return 400)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/conversation?limit=invalid

###

### GET /api/conversation - Error: Limit too high (should return 400)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/conversation?limit=5000

###

### DELETE /api/conversation/:conversationId - Delete a conversation by ID
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/conversation/some-conversation-id

###

### Complete workflow example:
### 1. Create a conversation (copy the returned id)
### 2. Add messages to that conversation
### 3. Get messages by conversation ID
### 4. Delete the conversation (cascades to messages)

### POST - Create conversation
POST http://localhost:3000/api/conversation
Content-Type: application/json

###

### POST - Add message to the created conversation (replace {conversation_id} with actual id)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/messages
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "Hello from the test suite!",
  "conversationId": "{conversation_id}",
  "role": 1
}

###

### GET - Get messages for this conversation
GET http://localhost:3000/api/messages/{conversation_id}

###

### DELETE - Delete the conversation
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/conversation/{conversation_id}
